On Jul 2, 2007, at 12:14 PM, Alan Beck wrote:

> My VW manual says to torque the nuts on the rocker arms of my Type  
> V engine
> to 260 inch pounds from 111 inch pounds.

Are you sure you're not reading the Type 1 specs? 10-11 ft.lbs is the  
spec.

> I am in the 180's now and I expect something to let go. It is  
> really tight
> and I am afraid to create a big problem.

Stop.

If you go too tight, you'll lock up the nut on the rocker arm shaft  
support and the stud will start to back out if you try to undo it.

